<p>Great! <em>We</em> know that this will be one of three special strings, either <code>normal</code>,
<code>no_jedi</code> or <code>only_jedi</code>. We can use those to change the behavior.</p>
<p>First, the two blocks near the top should <em>only</em> be run if Jedi powers are being
used. Add to the if statement: if <code>$battleType != 'no_jedi'</code>, then we can run this.
Copy that and add it to the second block:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="f304120f8d">
    <div class="meta">
        <div class="actions">
            <span class="fa fa-clipboard js-activate-clipboard" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Copy Code" data-placement="top"></span>
        </div>
        <div class="info">
                        <span class="js-expand-all" data-range="1-76" data-toggle="tooltip" title="Show All Lines" data-placement="top">
                <i class="fa fa-expand js-icon-load-more"></i>
                <i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin js-icon-loading"></i>
            </span>
            
            76 lines <span class="meta-divider"></span> <span title="lib/Service/BattleManager.php">lib/Service/BattleManager.php</span>
        </div>
    </div>
